# 🌌 SDSS Sky Object Classification

## 📌 Overview & Objective

This project focuses on classifying celestial objects using data from the **Sloan Digital Sky Survey (SDSS)**. The dataset contains astronomical observations with features derived from photometric measurements.

🎯 **Objective:**
Build a machine learning system capable of accurately classifying sky objects into:

* 🌠 **Galaxy**
* ⭐ **Star**
* 🌀 **Quasar**

This task is fundamental in astronomy for understanding the structure and evolution of the universe, while also serving as a strong applied ML classification problem.

---

## 🧰 Tech Stack

The system is built using a clean and modular stack:

* 🐍 **Python** — Core programming language
* 🤖 **scikit-learn** — Model training (Decision Tree, Logistic Regression, Random Forest)
* 🌐 **Flask** — Backend API for serving ML predictions
* 🎨 **Streamlit** — Interactive frontend UI for user input and visualization

---

## 🏗️ System Architecture

The project follows a **decoupled architecture**:

```
[Jupyter Notebook] → [Model Training & Evaluation]
                         ↓
                 [Saved Models (.pkl)]
                         ↓
                 [Flask API Backend]
                         ↓
                [Streamlit Frontend UI]
```

### Key Design Choices:

* 📦 ML logic is **extracted from notebooks** into reusable backend code
* 🔌 Flask acts as a **prediction service (API layer)**
* 🖥️ Streamlit provides a **user-friendly interface** for interaction
* 📊 Metrics are stored separately (`metrics.json`) for transparency

This separation ensures better scalability, maintainability, and real-world deployment alignment.

---

## 🚀 How to Run

### 1️⃣ Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd <your-project-folder>
```

---

### 2️⃣ Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

### 3️⃣ Run Backend (Flask API)

Open **Terminal 1**:

```bash
cd backend
python app.py
```

📍 The API will run at:

```
http://127.0.0.1:5000
```

---

### 4️⃣ Run Frontend (Streamlit)

Open **Terminal 2**:

```bash
cd frontend
streamlit run main.py
```

📍 The UI will open automatically in your browser:

```
http://localhost:8501
```

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```
backend/
  ├── models/
  │     ├── model_dt.pkl
  │     ├── model_logreg.pkl
  │     ├── model_rf.pkl
  │     ├── scaler_sdss.pkl
  │     └── metrics.json
  └── app.py

data/
  └── star_classification.csv

frontend/
  ├── main.py
  └── .streamlit/config.toml

notebooks/
  └── classification_comparison.ipynb

static/
  ├── images/
  └── style.css

templates/
  └── index.html

calc_metrics.py
README.md
requirements.txt
```

